"```sql\nSELECT \n    AVG(CASE WHEN Segment = 'SME' THEN Consumption END) AS SME_Average,\n    AVG(CASE WHEN Segment = 'LAM' THEN Consumption END) AS LAM_Average,\n    AVG(CASE WHEN Segment = 'KAM' THEN Consumption END) AS KAM_Average\nFROM \n    yearmonth\nJOIN \n    customers ON yearmonth.CustomerID = customers.CustomerID\nWHERE \n    Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'\nGROUP BY \n    Segment\nHAVING \n    Consumption = (SELECT MIN(Consumption) \n                   FROM yearmonth \n                   JOIN customers ON yearmonth.CustomerID = customers.CustomerID \n                   WHERE Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312' \n                   GROUP BY Segment);\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the annual average consumption for customers with the least amount of consumption in each segment (SME, LAM, KAM) for the year 2013. It uses a JOIN to connect the `yearmonth` and `customers` tables based on the `CustomerID`, filters the data for the year 2013, and groups the results by segment. The `HAVING` clause ensures that only the customers with the minimum consumption in each segment are considered."